		<div class="itemFullText">
			<h3>What is face recognition?</h3>
<p>The motive for writing this article was pretty simple. Amazon Rekognition, when I wandered around Amazon and tried to find a thing I did not necessarily need. After a moment of searching and wandering about what actually happens, I came across a very simple definition of how Rekognition actually works. This is Amazon Web Services (AWS) technology and workshop, which provides high-precision face analysis and face recognition on images and videos you provide. Amazon Rekognition is based on the highly scalable, learning-savvy technology developed by Amazon scientists. Based on analyzes of billions of images and videos daily, it does not require experience and expertise with machine learning systems. But the story does not end there. Forbes Magazine has decided to test this solution. He has found very interesting things, and so, besides a very cheap solution, this is an extremely accurate solution.</p>
<p>Based on photos voluntarily provided by staff in Jersey and London, the people around Thomas Fox-Brewster were able to put an extremely accurate Face Detection solution after a few hours. The first step was to set up the AWS database - "S3 bucket" with whom he has recorded various random photographs along with his employees' (Las Vegas criminals) photos. Rekognition does not have a simple face-to-face visualization and matching tool that results in text output. Therefore, with the help of an independent programmer, a simple script was written, marking a green square around the faces of the people who were not in the database or the red square of those who were in the database. In order for Rekognition to compare faces with databases, a "fake" record was recorded that simulated images from CCTV cameras. Based on the information provided by Thomas in his article, the results were surprising not only with their accuracy but also with the speed of response. What's even more remarkable is the price of a solution from AWS to solve this size, which according to published information would not exceed $ 10.</p>
<p>"Face recognition" technology is the technology capable of recognizing and identifying people from digital photos and face recognition videos. The way these systems work are a few but generally most of them work by comparing selected facial features from a given image with facial features within a database. Normally, this technology is used in security and security systems, but with the growing number of smart technologies, it is clear that the use of face recognition will be applicable in other areas as well. But the question remains security and protection of scrubs.</p>		</div>

		
